  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `docs/architecture/VISUALHOST-ARCHITECTURE.md` (HorizontalStackedBar Custom Options table — confirm the new `layoutMode`, `headlineFromField`, `subLineTemplate` keys are documented) and `docs/guides/VISUALHOST-SETUP-GUIDE.md` (HSBar authoring examples).</step>
    <step order="2">Verify task 023 (HorizontalStackedBar renderer extensions) has merged so `layoutMode: "headlineAboveBar"`, `headlineFromField`, `subLineTemplate` with `{remaining}` / `{percent}` / `{total}` placeholders are all live. If not, BLOCK and report to user.</step>
    <step order="3">Author the `sprk_chartdefinition` record using mcp__dataverse__create_record (or PowerShell + Web API). Fields: `sprk_name` = "Matter Budget", `sprk_visualtype` = 100000012, `sprk_entityname` = "sprk_matter", `sprk_optionsjson` = exact JSON from `<notes>` below, drill-through entity = `sprk_invoice`, drill-through filter field = `_sprk_matter_value`. Also configure the data source bindings for `sprk_totalspendtodate` (current value) and `sprk_totalbudget` (total) per the existing HSBar data-binding contract (see HorizontalStackedBar.tsx for the expected field-binding shape).</step>
    <step order="4">Verify the record was created by issuing `mcp__dataverse__read_query` for the new record id; confirm `sprk_optionsjson` round-trips identically.</step>
    <step order="5">Render verification: load a test Matter record with non-zero `sprk_totalspendtodate` and `sprk_totalbudget` in the dev environment; place a Visual Host instance bound to this chart def on a temporary form; confirm it renders `$50K`-style headline (or whatever the current value is, currency-formatted) + `33% of $150K`-style sub-line + a color-thresholded progress bar matching the Variant H prototype.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify the color thresholds: confirm that at low spend (&lt;60%) the bar is the success tokenSet; at 60-85% it's warning; at &gt;85% it's danger. (Either inspect three matters or temporarily mutate test data.)</step>
    <step order="7">Verify Drill Through: click expand on the rendered card; confirm it opens the `sprk_invoice` list filtered to the current matter.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 031 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__create_record">Create the sprk_chartdefinition record</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__read_query">Verify round-trip of sprk_optionsjson</tool>
